The Ultimate TikTok Video Building Prompt

Here's a comprehensive step-by-step prompt you can give to any AI bot to build a professional 15-second TikTok video:

MASTER PROMPT: Building a 15-Second TikTok Video

Imagine your video is a stage with invisible grid squares. Each element—text, emoji, filter, effect—is a physical block that sits on this stage. Your job is to place each block, tell it when to appear, how to move, and when to disappear. Every single element must have a start time, duration, motion type, and end time.

PHASE 1: FOUNDATION LAYER (0-15 seconds)

Block 1 - Background Filter/Video Base
What it is:** The main video clip or background filter
Start time:** 0 seconds
Motion:** Static (no movement) OR subtle zoom (0.5% scale increase per second)
Duration:** Full 15 seconds
End time:** 15 seconds
Why:** This is your canvas. Everything else layers on top.

PHASE 2: OPENING TRANSITION (0-1 second)

Block 2 - Opening Fade-In Effect
What it is:** A black or transparent overlay that fades away
Start time:** 0 seconds
Motion:** Opacity goes from 100% to 0% (fade out)
Duration:** 1 second
End time:** 1 second
Why:** Grabs attention instantly and creates professional polish

Block 3 - Opening Sticker or Logo
What it is:** A branded sticker, logo, or decorative element
Start time:** 0 seconds
Motion:** Scale animation—grows from 0% to 120% of full size, then settles to 100%
Duration:** 0.8 seconds
End time:** 0.8 seconds
Position:** Top-left or center corner
Why:** Immediately establishes brand or visual identity

PHASE 3: PRIMARY TEXT BLOCK (2-7 seconds)

Block 4 - Main Headline Text
What it is:** Your primary message (max 3-5 words)
Font:** Bold sans-serif (Arial, Montserrat, or similar)
Size:** Large enough to fill 40-50% of screen width
Start time:** 2 seconds
Entry motion:** Fade in + scale up simultaneously (opacity 0→100%, size 80%→100%)
Duration of animation:** 0.5 seconds
Hold time:** From 2.5 to 6.5 seconds (static display)
Exit motion:** At 6.5 seconds, fade out + slide up (opacity 100%→0%, position shifts up 50 pixels)
Duration of exit:** 0.5 seconds
End time:** 7 seconds
Color:** High contrast (white on dark background OR black on light—use a shadow layer for readability)
Position:** Vertical center, horizontal center
Why:** This is your hook—viewers have 2-3 seconds to read it

Block 5 - Secondary Supporting Text
What it is:** Secondary message or call-to-action (2-4 words)
Font:** Medium weight, 60% the size of primary text
Start time:** 4 seconds
Entry motion:** Slide up from bottom + fade in (Y position -100 pixels→0, opacity 0→100%)
Duration of animation:** 0.4 seconds
Hold time:** 4.4 to 8 seconds
Exit motion:** Slide down + fade out
Duration of exit:** 0.4 seconds
End time:** 8.4 seconds
Position:** Below primary text, 20 pixels gap
Why:** Reinforces message and adds depth

PHASE 4: EMOJI & STICKER LAYER (1-13 seconds)

Block 6 - Emoji #1 (Attention Grabber)
What it is:** A single large emoji (fire 🔥, star ⭐, or checkmark ✅)
Start time:** 1 second
Entry motion:** Scale + rotate (size 0%→120%, rotation 0°→360°)
Duration of animation:** 0.6 seconds
Hold time:** 1.6 to 5.5 seconds
Motion during hold:** Bounce effect—oscillate up and down 10 pixels, 0.4 second bounce cycle
Exit motion:** Scale down + fade (size 120%→0%, opacity 100%→0%)
Duration of exit:** 0.4 seconds
End time:** 6 seconds
Position:** Right side of screen, aligned with primary text
Why:** Adds visual pop and draws eye movement

Block 7 - Emoji #2 (Mid-Video Emphasis)
What it is:** Different emoji (heart ❤️, lightning ⚡, or sparkle ✨)
Start time:** 8 seconds
Entry motion:** Spin in from corner (rotation 180°→0°, scale 50%→100%)
Duration of animation:** 0.5 seconds
Hold time:** 8.5 to 12.5 seconds
Motion during hold:** Subtle float—moves up/down 8 pixels, 1 second cycle, continuous loop
Exit motion:** Fade out only
Duration of exit:** 0.5 seconds
End time:** 13 seconds
Position:** Left side of screen, lower position
Why:** Re-engages viewer at midpoint, prevents content fatigue

Block 8 - Decorative Sticker Elements
What it is:** 2-3 small background stickers (shapes, confetti, or thematic elements)
Start time:** 3 seconds
Entry motion:** Fade in only (opacity 0→100%)
Duration of animation:** 0.3 seconds
Hold time:** 3.3 to 8 seconds
Motion during hold:** Slow continuous rotation (5° per second)
Exit motion:** Fade out
Duration of exit:** 0.3 seconds
End time:** 8.3 seconds
Position:** Background—scattered, not blocking text
Opacity:** 40-60% (semi-transparent so they don't compete)
Why:** Fills dead space, adds visual texture without overwhelming

PHASE 5: TRANSITION EFFECTS (Mid-Video)

Block 9 - Mid-Video Transition Effect (6-7 seconds)
What it is:** A visual break effect (blur zoom, pixelate, or wipe transition)
Start time:** 6 seconds
Animation:** For blur zoom—scale from 100% to 110% while blur increases from 0 to 20px
Duration:** 1 second
Effect type:** Symmetrical (scales from center outward)
End time:** 7 seconds
Position:** Full screen overlay
Why:** Creates a professional "moment change" and maintains viewer attention

PHASE 6: KINETIC TEXT LAYER (5-12 seconds)

Block 10 - Kinetic Typography Overlay
What it is:** Animated words that appear and move with the beat
Start time:** 5 seconds
Animation type:** Word-by-word entrance, staggered by 0.2 seconds
Motion:** Each word slides in from left, rotates slightly (5°), then snaps to center
Duration per word animation:** 0.3 seconds
Hold time:** Each word stays 1.5 seconds
Exit:** Slides out to right while fading
Duration of exit:** 0.3 seconds
End time:** 12 seconds
Font:** Thin, modern (Futura, Quicksand, or similar)
Color:** Neon or contrasting color to primary text
Why:** Creates rhythm synced to music and maintains dynamic feel

PHASE 7: MUSIC SYNC MARKERS (Audio-Visual Sync)

Block 11-14 - Beat Sync Points (Invisible but Critical)
Sync Point 1 (0 seconds):** Beat drop/intro—coincides with opening fade-in
Sync Point 2 (4 seconds):** Bass hit—emoji #1 bounces extra large, primary text pulses
Sync Point 3 (8 seconds):** Secondary beat drop—emoji #2 enters, transition occurs
Sync Point 4 (12 seconds):** Final build—all elements intensify (opacity increases 10%, scale +5%)
Why:** Audio-visual synchronization is the #1 factor determining viral TikTok success

PHASE 8: CLOSING SEQUENCE (13-15 seconds)

Block 15 - Call-to-Action Text
What it is:** Final message ("Follow," "Shop Now," "Learn More," or question)
Start time:** 13 seconds
Entry motion:** Zoom in from center (scale 0%→100%, opacity 0→100%)
Duration of animation:** 0.4 seconds
Hold time:** 13.4 to 14.5 seconds
Font:** Bold, large, 80% of primary text size
Color:** Bright accent color (red, neon pink, or gold)
Position:** Lower third of screen, centered
Exit motion:** Fade out only
Duration of exit:** 0.5 seconds
End time:** 15 seconds
Why:** Last impression—viewers are most likely to act on final frames

Block 16 - Closing Transition (Fade to Black)
What it is:** Black or dark overlay fade-out
Start time:** 14 seconds
Motion:** Opacity 0→100%
Duration:** 1 second
End time:** 15 seconds
Why:** Professional ending, stops abrupt cuts

Block 17 - End Screen Sticker
What it is:** Single element promoting next action (Follow button, "Check my profile," etc.)
Start time:** 14.5 seconds
Entry motion:** Bounce scale (size 0%→110%→100%)
Duration of animation:** 0.4 seconds
Hold time:** 14.9 to 15 seconds
Position:** Center or bottom-right
Why:** Directs viewer to next action immediately after video ends

