TIMING OVERLAP RULES

Layers should overlap intentionally.** Primary text (2-7s) overlaps with secondary text (4-8.4s), emojis (1-6s and 8-13s), and background stickers (3-8.3s). This creates depth.
Transitions prevent overlap collisions.** The mid-video transition (6-7s) creates a "reset moment" where old elements fade and new ones can enter.
No more than 4 animated elements at once.** Too many simultaneous motions create visual chaos. Stagger entries by 0.5-2 seconds.

FINAL EXPORT SETTINGS

Resolution:** 1080 x 1920 pixels (vertical format)
Frame rate:** 30 FPS (smooth motion)
Duration:** Exactly 15 seconds
Audio:** Trending audio synced to beat markers
Colors:** 3-4 color palette maximum (prevents visual overwhelm)

